summary: REQ-15 appears implemented in SiteHeader with an Instagram external link in both desktop nav and mobile menu, using SITE_CONFIG.instagram.url and opening in a new tab with rel="noopener noreferrer". REQ-16 is partially evidenced: SITE_CONFIG.instagram.url is set to the required canonical URL, and the header uses it; however, there is no diff evidence that the footer uses the same configuration value or that its Instagram link was updated/verified.

missing_requirements.requirement: Ensure the footer Instagram link uses the canonical SITE_CONFIG.instagram.url value (no hardcoded duplicate URL) and points to https://www.instagram.com/herwellness_2026/.
missing_requirements.reason: The diff shows SITE_CONFIG updated and SiteHeader consuming SITE_CONFIG.instagram.url, but there are no changes shown for SiteFooter and no direct evidence that the footer link uses SITE_CONFIG.instagram.url or that it now points to the updated URL.
evidence: frontend-file-summaries.txt (mentions SiteFooter but no code diff for it)
